WEBVTT

00:00.962 --> 00:04.125
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:04.686 --> 00:18.380
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:19.121 --> 00:26.649
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:26.709 --> 00:27.890
Today,

00:27.970 --> 00:35.983
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:40.591 --> 00:41.192
Peace be with you.

00:41.232 --> 00:48.023
Friends, we come to the final weekend of the surgical year, which means it's time to celebrate the Feast of Christ, the King.

00:48.083 --> 00:52.370
And I know every time I come to this feast, you face a certain dilemma because

00:52.610 --> 00:54.012
You know, we don't like kings.

00:54.652 --> 00:57.335
Our country was formed in a rebellion against a king.

00:57.415 --> 00:58.797
You say, well, look, I'm not a king.

00:58.817 --> 00:59.398
I don't know.

00:59.438 --> 01:00.219
Anyone was a king.

01:00.279 --> 01:02.241
And so I say Christ is king.

01:02.281 --> 01:03.843
All right, I guess.

01:03.903 --> 01:05.404
But what does it have to do with me, right?

01:05.925 --> 01:09.669
Well, actually, if we understand this properly, it has everything to do with us.

01:10.530 --> 01:16.817
Can I ask you maybe just for a moment to bracket the explicitly political side of kingship and think of it this way.

01:17.618 --> 01:21.042
A king is someone who orders things

01:21.442 --> 01:22.443
towards an end.

01:23.745 --> 01:25.528
Think here of like an orchestra conductor.

01:26.169 --> 01:29.513
He's got all the players and all the instruments in front of him.

01:29.533 --> 01:38.446
He's not making a sound himself, but he's ordering all these things toward the end of producing Beethoven's Fifth Symphony or something.

01:38.466 --> 01:41.270
Think of a general of an army.

01:42.051 --> 01:50.162
He doesn't himself fire a shot, but he's coordinating all of the elements of the army to achieve the great end of victory and battle.

01:50.914 --> 02:00.226
Think of the father of a family who is trying to order the carisms that are before him toward the end of the flourishing of his family.

02:01.407 --> 02:05.612
That's a king, someone that orders things towards a proper end.

02:05.833 --> 02:09.858
Now you can begin to see, well look, a lot of us play kingly roles.

02:10.639 --> 02:13.983
That might not be king of the world, but we're king of our family.

02:14.023 --> 02:16.767
We play a kingly role often in our communities.

02:17.147 --> 02:19.570
We can play a kingly role among our friends.

02:19.970 --> 02:21.092
And here's the thing.

02:22.534 --> 02:26.861
Every one of us plays a kingly role in regard to ourselves.

02:28.684 --> 02:38.860
Look, I'm made up of all these different energies and capacities and instincts and inclinations and they go in different directions, right?

02:38.960 --> 02:40.463
Plato recognized that a long time ago.

02:40.483 --> 02:42.546
They're like horses that are going in different directions.

02:42.926 --> 02:45.170
The horses need a charioteer

02:45.378 --> 02:45.718
Right?

02:45.899 --> 02:49.264
Who's going to draw them together and lead them to a common purpose?

02:49.704 --> 02:58.297
So my soul needs a king that will direct all these energies in the right way.

02:59.478 --> 03:00.400
Now, what's the right way?

03:00.860 --> 03:02.102
Well, think about this now.

03:03.164 --> 03:08.471
Certainly everyone listened to me who was baptized a Catholic as part of the ceremony.

03:08.872 --> 03:12.978
So of course, water is poured over your head, but as part of the ceremony,

03:13.314 --> 03:16.779
You were chrismated on the crown of your head.

03:17.861 --> 03:34.305
Chrism oil used in the anointing of kings on the crown of your head, because as baptized, you are conformed to Christ who is priest, prophet, and king.

03:35.287 --> 03:39.173
So every baptized person, listen to me, you're a king.

03:39.714 --> 03:42.738
Whether you like political kings or not, you're a king.

03:43.234 --> 03:46.800
You are conformed to Christ in His kingly identity.

03:47.541 --> 03:48.302
What's your job?

03:48.683 --> 03:55.613
Well, wherever God puts you, to order things toward the end of God's kingdom.

03:56.515 --> 03:59.459
And that means first and foremost, you.

04:00.581 --> 04:03.025
You got to order yourself properly.

04:03.846 --> 04:06.290
Okay, with that clarification in mind,

04:06.850 --> 04:13.300
Let's look at some kings in the Bible because the Bible is massively interested in kings.

04:14.401 --> 04:19.549
And then once we understand what kingship means for us spiritually, this can be super helpful to us.

04:20.711 --> 04:24.036
First of all, first king in the Bible, Adam.

04:25.458 --> 04:29.824
Adam is meant to be the one who cultivates the garden.

04:30.926 --> 04:33.810
Listen now, who protects the garden,

04:34.626 --> 04:37.309
and then pushes the boundaries of the garden outward.

04:38.390 --> 04:40.953
So Adam is planted and eaten by God.

04:41.013 --> 04:43.316
Now we're using highly symbolic language here.

04:44.177 --> 04:54.549
His purpose is now to cultivate it, make it even more beautiful place and to keep out of it, things that will interrupt its beauty and its proper functioning.

04:55.270 --> 04:58.994
And then go on the march and spread its boundaries outward.

05:00.002 --> 05:00.402
All right.

05:00.783 --> 05:01.644
Was he a good king?

05:01.664 --> 05:03.526
No, he was a failed king.

05:03.546 --> 05:06.930
And in many ways, that's the very essence of original sin.

05:06.990 --> 05:09.012
What does Adam fail to do?

05:09.072 --> 05:11.575
He fails to defend the garden against the serpent.

05:12.296 --> 05:17.382
So he allows corruption to come into this beautiful place.

05:18.784 --> 05:21.046
And thereby he's expelled from the garden.

05:22.468 --> 05:23.509
He's a failed king.

05:23.549 --> 05:27.954
Now, think about in terms of your own, your own life.

05:29.634 --> 05:39.670
Do we sometimes fail in our cultivation of the garden, which is our own soul and fellow sinners?

05:39.690 --> 05:47.763
Do we fail in protecting that flourishing garden from enemies and from temptations?

05:49.406 --> 05:56.978
How often we get off the rail because we succumb, as Adam did, to petty, pathetic temptations

05:57.794 --> 06:01.880
toward wealth or power or my own ego or honors or whatever it is.

06:01.900 --> 06:08.208
And when I allow those temptations into my soul, then my soul becomes disordered.

06:08.749 --> 06:09.771
I'm a bad king.

06:09.811 --> 06:15.078
And therefore, I don't spread good order around me.

06:15.258 --> 06:18.523
In fact, I become a source of disorder for others.

06:19.244 --> 06:21.988
Huh, Adam failed king.

06:22.929 --> 06:25.132
All right, now watch as we move through the Old Testament.

06:26.013 --> 06:26.674
Israel

06:27.202 --> 06:29.845
always searching for a true king.

06:31.387 --> 06:34.591
Look at Abraham, our father in faith, right?

06:34.631 --> 06:37.134
The founder, really, of the people Israel.

06:38.775 --> 06:39.717
What's his great virtue?

06:41.459 --> 06:42.740
He listens to a higher voice.

06:44.642 --> 06:49.748
He hears the voice of the Lord, and he obeys it, even though it's calling him to a very difficult task.

06:49.808 --> 06:54.674
Leave your homeland, leave everyone you know, and go in search of this promised land.

06:54.786 --> 07:03.661
Abraham listens to a higher voice than the little voice of his own ego and his own ambitions and his own projects and plans.

07:04.041 --> 07:05.323
He listens to God's voice.

07:06.385 --> 07:14.979
And in that measure, he becomes a good king of his own life and of the lives of those around him.

07:15.841 --> 07:18.986
There's an old adage from Benjamin Franklin.

07:19.006 --> 07:21.650
I remember reading it as a little kid and the adages

07:22.434 --> 07:26.340
The one who cannot obey cannot command.

07:27.682 --> 07:28.583
It's always struck me as right.

07:29.345 --> 07:30.266
And it applies here.

07:30.326 --> 07:41.303
If you can't obey, listen to the higher voice of God, you're in no position to command yourself, your family, your community, or anybody else.

07:41.904 --> 07:43.066
It was a great lesson of Abraham.

07:44.849 --> 07:45.510
How about David?

07:46.551 --> 07:48.434
The greatest king we could say in Israel.

07:48.802 --> 07:51.485
Does David at his best listen to God's voice?

07:51.645 --> 07:53.547
Yeah, read those stories again.

07:53.868 --> 07:56.430
When David attends to God's voice, things go well.

07:57.472 --> 07:59.714
Secondly, is David a warrior?

08:00.935 --> 08:02.517
Like all the kings of Israel.

08:03.218 --> 08:05.781
Moses is a kind of king and he's a warrior.

08:06.522 --> 08:10.286
Joshua, look at all the great figures, the great kingly figures.

08:10.326 --> 08:11.867
They're all fighters.

08:14.570 --> 08:17.874
Adam didn't fight what he should have fought.

08:19.298 --> 08:19.839
Right?

08:19.859 --> 08:21.641
He should have resisted the devil.

08:21.821 --> 08:22.402
He didn't, though.

08:22.422 --> 08:23.122
He didn't fight him.

08:24.284 --> 08:25.205
That was his downfall.

08:26.046 --> 08:28.789
All the great kings of Israel are willing to battle.

08:29.029 --> 08:33.754
Now, don't get hung up, you know, I'm talking about taking up violent weapons, necessarily.

08:33.854 --> 08:40.362
I just mean, are you willing to resist the evil that has to be resisted?

08:41.523 --> 08:43.005
Do you stand up to it?

08:43.786 --> 08:47.570
Do you have the valor and the courage to face down evil?

08:48.002 --> 08:53.928
Look, if you don't do it in your own life, you don't defend your own soul against evil, then you'll be a lousy king.

08:55.149 --> 09:02.557
You don't defend your community, your society, your culture, your country against evil, you're a bad king.

09:02.617 --> 09:05.459
All the great kings are fighters.

09:06.561 --> 09:08.002
Now, mind you, stay with David.

09:08.923 --> 09:10.244
When is David becoming a bad king?

09:11.746 --> 09:16.050
When he stops listening to God and starts acting like God.

09:16.610 --> 09:18.772
think you're the famous Bathsheba story, right?

09:19.253 --> 09:22.356
David now acting like God, up on his roof.

09:22.416 --> 09:23.597
No, there's this beautiful woman.

09:23.617 --> 09:24.058
I want her.

09:24.078 --> 09:24.799
Well, she's married.

09:24.839 --> 09:25.339
I don't care.

09:25.379 --> 09:30.885
David acting like God rather than listening to God.

09:32.066 --> 09:33.247
That's where kings go bad.

09:34.389 --> 09:38.573
Be attentive to that now, fellow baptized people, all called to be kings.

09:40.535 --> 09:42.217
How about David's son Solomon?

09:42.377 --> 09:43.378
Now Solomon,

09:43.522 --> 09:46.526
like a lot of the kings of Israel does go bad in time.

09:47.107 --> 09:49.571
But in the beginning, Solomon's a very good king indeed.

09:50.673 --> 09:51.213
What does he do?

09:51.334 --> 09:52.656
Well, he builds the temple.

09:53.697 --> 09:59.606
Notice, please, first of all, the temple that the king of Israel prioritizes right praise.

10:00.267 --> 10:06.556
See, again, listening to God's voice, that's what's paramount when it comes to proper spiritual leadership.

10:06.977 --> 10:09.280
You don't listen to God's voice, you'll be a lousy leader.

10:09.380 --> 10:13.106
So Solomon appropriately builds a place of praise.

10:13.282 --> 10:17.786
But secondly, think about the temple simply as a building project.

10:18.487 --> 10:26.915
How involved that is, how complicated and, you know, wood from Lebanon and workers from here and there and material from all over the place.

10:26.995 --> 10:31.759
And Solomon is the one who is organizing it according to this great purpose.

10:33.221 --> 10:34.422
What's his mark, by the way?

10:34.462 --> 10:35.443
What's he most famous for?

10:35.523 --> 10:37.185
Wisdom.

10:38.386 --> 10:40.448
Solomon is the archetype of wisdom.

10:41.048 --> 10:42.930
What's wisdom is this

10:43.106 --> 10:52.755
view from the hilltop, Aquinas says, seeing life from the standpoint of the highest cause, seeing, listen now, the great pattern of things.

10:53.977 --> 11:05.007
You can't be a king, you can't be a good leader unless you've got a vision of what things are supposed to be, unless you see everything from the standpoint of God.

11:05.908 --> 11:09.171
Ah, there's Solomon in his wisdom.

11:10.152 --> 11:11.954
So listening to a higher voice,

11:12.194 --> 11:22.584
making the praise of God paramount, being valorous, courageous, willing to resist evil, be a warrior, be a person of wisdom, able to organize these great projects.

11:23.485 --> 11:25.668
Yeah, those are all the marks of a king.

11:26.789 --> 11:28.991
Now, who's the king of kings?

11:30.432 --> 11:33.395
Who is the one to whom all these Old Testament kings are pointing?

11:34.597 --> 11:37.099
Christ the king whom we celebrate today.

11:38.581 --> 11:40.082
Warrior, you bet.

11:40.386 --> 11:47.316
Watch Jesus now up and down the gospels, not with the weapons of the world, but battling evil when it needs to be battled.

11:47.897 --> 11:50.481
Even in the face of great opposition, criticism, you bet.

11:50.861 --> 11:55.809
The cross, Jesus doing battle finally with sin and death themselves.

11:56.650 --> 11:58.252
Jesus warrior for sure.

11:59.294 --> 12:05.042
Jesus who listens to the higher voice, well, I only do what I see my father doing.

12:05.602 --> 12:13.071
My food is to do the will of my heavenly father, not what I will, but what you will, attention to the higher voice.

12:14.032 --> 12:14.492
Wisdom?

12:15.073 --> 12:19.198
Well, not only is he a wise person, he's wisdom incarnate.

12:19.758 --> 12:22.061
We say he's the logos made flesh.

12:23.303 --> 12:27.487
So in all these ways, everybody, Christ is the king of kings.

12:27.567 --> 12:33.234
He's the king for which Israel was longing from the time of Adam on.

12:33.698 --> 12:37.583
All the figures I mentioned from the Old Testament are anticipations of Him.

12:38.785 --> 12:40.708
Now, bring it back home to us.

12:41.449 --> 12:54.787
So on this feast of Christ, the King, we who are all kings, not in the grandest possible way, but at the very least, we're kings of our own souls, we're kings of our own lives.

12:56.389 --> 12:57.030
What do we find?

12:58.532 --> 12:59.473
These same principles.

13:01.496 --> 13:02.898
Do you listen to a higher voice

13:03.522 --> 13:06.085
Or is your own voice what's most important to you?

13:06.566 --> 13:10.652
Your own projects, your own plans, what I want, what I... No, no, no.

13:11.072 --> 13:12.935
He who cannot obey cannot command.

13:13.315 --> 13:17.241
You won't command your own life unless you're listening to a higher voice.

13:17.601 --> 13:20.064
Is worship central to your life?

13:22.067 --> 13:22.888
Are you a warrior?

13:23.970 --> 13:27.154
Or like Adam, do you shrink from the fight?

13:28.034 --> 13:35.242
Do you give in to those petty temptations that are keeping you from being the person God wants you to be?

13:35.282 --> 13:37.124
Or do you stand up to them?

13:37.665 --> 13:41.710
See, kings who aren't willing to fight are by definition bad kings.

13:42.470 --> 13:56.146
I think very often fellow senators, what we do is we, like David, at the beginning of that Bathsheba story, it says, the time of year when kings go on campaign, as David always did,

13:56.930 --> 14:02.155
David was home taking a siesta on the roof of his palace.

14:02.816 --> 14:07.300
See, when David declined to fight, he becomes a bad king.

14:08.722 --> 14:14.287
Are we people of wisdom like Solomon, like Jesus' wisdom made flesh?

14:14.307 --> 14:15.569
Do we see our lives?

14:15.649 --> 14:18.531
Do we see reality from the standpoint of the highest cause?

14:20.373 --> 14:25.138
Take the time, everybody, today to meditate a bit upon these Old Testament kings

14:25.570 --> 14:36.001
all of whom lead to Christ the King, who is the model for all of us, baptized as priests, prophets, and kings.

14:37.002 --> 14:37.583
And God bless you.

14:42.128 --> 14:45.732
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron.

14:46.112 --> 14:51.218
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.

